United States. Circuit Court (District of Columbia) - Washington (D.C.)

In the foregoing cases, Alexander Waugh, the Defendant, by Philip R. Fendall, his attorney comes into Court, and says that he has not, nor claims to have any property in the petitioners or any of them, but the same to absolutely disavows and disclaims. P. R. Fendall Atty for A. Waugh April 30. 1835. filed 1st May 1835
United States. Circuit Court (District of Columbia) - Washington (D.C.)
